It would be awesome to optimize `custom_code`. Sometimes it works slowly.

Current implementation:
```python
def custom_code(mask: str = '@###',
                char: str = '@', digit: str = '#') -> str:
    code = ''
    for p in mask:
        if p == char:
            code += choice(string.ascii_uppercase)
        elif p == digit:
            code += str(randint(0, 9))
        else:
            code += p
    return code
```

